{"TopicId":163353,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"How do I find the highest terrain point on a celestrial body?","CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T12:39:52Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T12:39:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m trying to programically determine the \u0027low orbit\u0027 of a body, which is 10km above the highest surface peak\u00A0or above it\u0027s atmosphere, which ever is greater.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut, I don\u0027t know how to [quickly] find the highest terrestrial point. anyone know?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-17T12:40:44Z\u0022 title=\u002207/17/2017 12:40  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 17, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Xyphos\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Benjamin Kerman","CreatedById":172792,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T13:51:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry this:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/7542-the-official-unoffical-quothelp-a-fellow-plugin-developerquot-thread/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3111136\u0026amp;embedComment=3111136\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T13:59:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223123412\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163353\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221500299485\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022172792\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Benjamin Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Benjamin Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry this:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnope, I\u0027m not getting the distance from the active vessel, I\u0027m computing the highest point of a celestrial body\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nascarlaser1","CreatedById":166190,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T14:08:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf your looking for it for stock planets the wiki tells you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T14:08:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnevermind, I\u0027ve decided to simply add 20Km from sea-level radius, as nothing (I know of) will even reach that high, and only 10Km for bodies with atmospheres.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T14:15:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI used CelestialBody.atmosphereDepth or CelestialBody.minOrbitalDistance, depending on whether there\u0027s an atmosphere:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/HebaruSan/Astrogator/blob/master/src/KerbalTools.cs#L170-L177\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/HebaruSan/Astrogator/blob/master/src/KerbalTools.cs#L170-L177\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aelfhe1m","CreatedById":142910,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T14:21:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat shou\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223123429\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163353\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221500300511\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139010\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xyphos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, Xyphos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnevermind, I\u0027ve decided to simply add 20Km from sea-level radius, as nothing (I know of) will even reach that high, and only 10Km for bodies with atmospheres.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat should work for stock and similarly sized planet packs but may not cover every eventuality (especially in real scale systems - highest \u0022mountains\u0022 in the real life solar system are 22km on Vesta and 20km on Iapetus don\u0027t know if these are reflected in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaven\u0027t tested in game but did you look at CelestialBody.getBounds().max ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-17T14:23:06Z\u0022 title=\u002207/17/2017 02:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 17, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Aelfhe1m\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T14:28:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223123434\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163353\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221500300904\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI used CelestialBody.atmosphereDepth or CelestialBody.minOrbitalDistance, depending on whether there\u0027s an atmosphere:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/HebaruSan/Astrogator/blob/master/src/KerbalTools.cs#L170-L177\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/HebaruSan/Astrogator/blob/master/src/KerbalTools.cs#L170-L177\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh, that should work, thanks!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223123442\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163353\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221500301305\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022142910\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aelfhe1m\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Aelfhe1m said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat shou\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat should work for stock and similarly sized planet packs but may not cover every eventuality (especially in real scale systems - highest \u0022mountains\u0022 in the real life solar system are 22km on Vesta and 20km on Iapetus don\u0027t know if these are reflected in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaven\u0027t tested in game but did you look at CelestialBody.getBounds().max ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngood point, and IDK about getBounds.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aelfhe1m","CreatedById":142910,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T14:34:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223123434\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163353\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221500300904\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI used CelestialBody.atmosphereDepth or CelestialBody.minOrbitalDistance, depending on whether there\u0027s an atmosphere:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/HebaruSan/Astrogator/blob/master/src/KerbalTools.cs#L170-L177\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/HebaruSan/Astrogator/blob/master/src/KerbalTools.cs#L170-L177\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOut of curiosity, any idea what that gives for Gilly? I ask because the science low space threshold is lower than the highest elevation making getting low orbital science something you need to be careful about (or only do while also landing).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T14:50:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223123457\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163353\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221500302073\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022142910\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aelfhe1m\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, Aelfhe1m said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOut of curiosity, any idea what that gives for Gilly?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsnippet from my code:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E{\n                const double addedAltitude = 10000;\n\n                Name = body.bodyName;\n                GeeASL = body.GeeASL * G;\n                Selected = body.isHomeWorld;// Name.Equals(\u0022Kerbin\u0022);\n\n                var R = body.Radius \u002B (body.atmosphere ? body.atmosphereDepth : body.minOrbitalDistance) \u002B addedAltitude;\n                var C = Math.PI * (R * R);\n                Log(\u0022R: {0}\u0022, R);\n           }\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand the output from my debug log:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003E\nGilly     G=0.0490667567239553\nR: 680000\n\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aelfhe1m","CreatedById":142910,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T15:01:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223123471\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163353\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221500303046\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139010\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xyphos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Xyphos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nR: 680000\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nErr, is that maybe a mistype? Because Gilly\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E (according to the wiki) is only 126km.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T15:15:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223123490\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022163353\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221500303664\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022142910\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aelfhe1m\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, Aelfhe1m said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nErr, is that maybe a mistype? Because Gilly\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E (according to the wiki) is only 126km.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, that looks like the value for Kerbin to me. 600000 radius \u002B 70000 atmosphere \u002B 10000 padding = 680000.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T15:24:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003ER: 56000\nGilly     G=0.0490667567239553\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyeah, that was a mis-paste \u00A0 the R goes before the body name... (body name is logged outside the constructor...)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DMagic","CreatedById":57416,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-17T15:34:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe FinePrint.Utilities.CelestialUtilities\u00A0class has a method for this: GetHighestPeak(CelesitalBody body).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt should give you what you need, though it doesn\u0027t tell you anything about the atmosphere, that would have to be considered separately.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OhioBob","CreatedById":128005,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-18T22:17:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNevermind.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-18T22:25:06Z\u0022 title=\u002207/18/2017 10:25  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 18, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by OhioBob\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}